<headline>Severe Weather Statement issued April 15 at 3:56PM CDT until April 15 at 7:00PM CDT by NWS Tulsa</headline>
<description>...A SEVERE THUNDERSTORM WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 415 PM CDT
FOR SOUTHWESTERN MADISON COUNTY...
At 355 PM CDT, a severe thunderstorm was located near Japton, moving
northeast at 45 mph.
HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts and quarter size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Hail damage to vehicles is expected. Expect wind damage to
roofs, siding, and trees.
Locations in or near the path include...
Huntsville...                     Withrow Springs State Park...
Wesley...                         Aurora...
Japton...                         Witter...
Georgetown...                     Alabam...
HAIL THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX HAIL SIZE...1.00 IN
WIND THREAT...RADAR INDICATED
MAX WIND GUST...60 MPH</description>
<instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
